Activity Guide 3: Power App Enhancements

Module/Activity SubTitle/Short Description

Experience level:  Novice


Improve your Power App's form submission experience by creating a confirmation screen for user feedback after a user submits their form, resets the New Form, and creates new navigation to return to the landing page.

Confirm you are logged in to Power Apps Studio at and the Travel Request - YourInitials app is open for editing.

  1. Add a new screen and apply the Success template Show Me
  2. Select + New Screen to add another screen, scroll down (or type su in the search field) and select the Success template Show Me
  3. In the Tree view pane, below the search box, Select + New Screen to add another screen, scroll down (or type su in the search field) and select the Success template Show Me
  4. Rename your new screen to Confirmation Screen Show Me
  5. Click the ellipsis to the right of your new screen control, use the Rename option, change the name to Confirmation Screen Show Me
  6. In the Tree View pane, click the ellipsis to the right of your new screen control, use the Rename option, change the name to Confirmation Screen Show Me
  7. Set the Fill property to Green on the iconCircIe1 control which is contained by the Confirmation Screen control Show Me
  8. Expand Confirmation Screen, select iconCircIe1, select the Fill property and set the value in the formula bar to Color.Green Show Me
  9. Use the Tree view to expand Confirmation Screen, then select iconCircIe1 below the confirmation screen, and use the property selector to change the Fill color to Color.Green Show Me

  1. Add a Home Icon to the Confirmation Screen Show Me
  2. With the Confirmation screen selected, click + Insert > Icons > Home Show Me
  3. With the Confirmation Screen selected in Tree View, click + Insert > Icons > Home to add a Home icon to the screen Show Me
  4. Rename your icon to icnHome Show Me
  5. Click the ellipsis to the right of your new icon, use the Rename option, change the name to icnHome Show Me
  6. In the Tree View pane, click the ellipsis to the right of your new icon, use the Rename option, change the name to icnHome Show Me
  7. Update the OnSelect property for your Home Icon to Navigate('Main Screen',ScreenTransition.Fade) Show Me
  8. Click icnHome, using the property selector, select the OnSelect property and set the formula to Navigate('Main Screen',ScreenTransition.Fade) Show Me
  9. In Tree View, click icnHome, then using the property selector, select OnSelect and set the formula to Navigate('Main Screen',ScreenTransition.Fade) Show Me

  1. Set the OnVisible property of the New Request Screen to NewForm(frmNewRequestForm) Show Me
  2. Select the New Request Screen, use the property selector to select OnVisible and set the formula to NewForm(frmNewRequestForm) Show Me
  3. In Tree View, click New Request Screen, then using the property selector, select OnVisible and set the formula to NewForm(frmNewRequestForm) Show Me
  4. Set the OnSuccess property of frmNewRequestForm to NewForm(frmNewRequestForm); Navigate('Confirmation Screen') Show Me
  5. Select frmNewRequestForm nested below the New Request Screen, set the OnSuccess property to NewForm(frmNewRequestForm); Navigate('Confirmation Screen') Show Me
  6. Expand the New Request Screen, select frmNewRequestForm, Use the property selector to seselect the OnSuccess property to NewForm(frmNewRequestForm); Navigate('Confirmation Screen') Show Me
  7. Select the Main Screen, then run the app and test. Show Me
  8. Test the changes.
    • Click on the Main Screen
    • Click the Play button
    • Submit an entry
    • Navigate back to the Main Screen using the Home button on the success screen
     Show Me
  9. Let's test the changes.
    • Click on the Main Screen
    • Click the Play button
    • Submit an entry
    • Navigate back to the Main Screen using the Home button on the success screen
     Show Me
